node.text:
The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. This walkway is situated at 2,168 meters above sea level (7,112 ft). Would you go explore this region with 300 kilometres (187 miles) of hiking trails? ⁣
⁣
📌Grindelwald, Switzerland 🇨🇭⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @michelphotographych for your great video!⁣
⁣
⁣✅ If you want to be featured too, don't forget to follow @hikingtheglobe and tag # hikingtheglobe in your photos. Cheers!⁣
⁣

Finland is Europe’s most forested country, with about 70% of its land is covered with trees. Finland is also reputed to be the Land of a Thousand Lakes, but in fact the country has tens of thousands of lakes. Simply put, the Finnish countryside offers nature-lovers many different kinds of experiences. And thanks to free public access, hikers can roam the great outdoors nearly everywhere in Finland.⁣
⁣
📌 Finland 🇫🇮⁣

The Faroe Islands are one of the most remote and isolated places in the world and a week-long hiking trip allows travelers to venture off the beaten path into landscapes so otherworldly it’ll feel like you stepped into a fairytale. Mountains look like they have been planted in the ocean and plummeting fjords and craggy cliffs radiate with adventure. Hiking the Faroe Islands winds through picturesque villages and jaw-dropping natural wonders.⁣
⁣

The Canadian Rockies stretch 900 miles northwest from the Montana border. They began forming around 80 million years ago, making them 400 million years younger than the Appalachians. Their relative youth shows in their sharper edges and rough faces that contrast beautifully with the smooth lines of the glacial lakes they hold. These can take on downright surreal colors thanks to the microscopic bits of ground-up mountain that come off a glacier when it melts.⁣
⁣
📌 Quarry Lake, Canmore, Canada 🇨🇦⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @jasonmengvisuals and @laurenmneves for your great reel!⁣
⁣
✅ If you want to be featured too, don't forget to follow @hikingtheglobe and tag # hikingtheglobe. Cheers!

From coastal rainforests and arctic tundra to glaciers and towering mountain peaks, America’s Last Frontier offers exceptional hiking opportunities. Summer season runs from mid May to mid September with average temperatures in the 60’s to low 70’s Fahrenheit (15 - 22 Celsius), 16–24 hours of daylight, leaves and flowers in bloom, rushing rivers, and the best wildlife viewing.⁣

The Himalayas is the highest mountain range in the world, and has 9 out of 10 of the world’s highest peaks, including Mount Everest. These mountains, referred to as the Third Pole, are the source of some of Asia’s major rivers and also help to regulate our planet’s climate. For centuries people here have developed a unique culture that weaves nature and people together into the same fabric of life. The region is the birthplace of the Buddha, and is full of sacred natural sites such as secret valleys and high mountain lakes.⁣
⁣
📌 Nepal 🇳🇵⁣
⁣
📸 Thank you @jimmychin @black.sail_ @__sandeep_rai @sowhatwetravel @antonganja @anna_lankovich @andrii_lutsyk @eliasaikaly and @rawmeyn for your great photos!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

Romania is a great destination for hiking, mountaineering and all sorts of outdoor adventures and sports – yet few travellers are aware of this. ⁣
